# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- We will simply add add the values of nums[] in the hashset, then we will declare an  integer variable and initialize it with 1.

- So it is clear that if an array conatins of counting numbers from 1 the max it can have is the length of the array.

- So we'll check for all the integers from 1 to nums.length if anyone is missing simply return it otherwise return nums.length +1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

