## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- First, we store the minimum value in ***mn*** & in between make all values 1 which are less than 1 or greater than n.
- **The logic behind it:** if the array is size n, then max possible n positive character. if any value is greater than n, then there is already an element from 1 to n that is not present.
- After the loop ends, if we find ***mn is greater than 1***, that means 1 is not present & simply ***return 1***.
- Else we’ll iterate again & go to the index from elements and if it’s not negative then make it negative.
- Again iterate all elements & the first index where ***the element is positive***, which means that element is not present. So ***return i+1***.
- Still, we iterate all elements and didn’t find the ans that means elements are from 1 to n, in the array, so return ***n+1***.
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

