# Approach
Steps:
1.remove all the elements having zero or negative value.
2.sort the new array and remove all the duplicates.
3.now, array has all the element are unique +ve & in increasing order.
4.run the loop & check the condition v[i]==i+1,if this fails,answer is i+1,return it.otherwise answer will be v.size()+1.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(nlog(n))

- Space complexity:
O(1)

