# Bruteforce
Mark all the integers of array in separate array of n elements by updating corresponding value to 1 and then from start find index at which value is not 1 to identify the smallest missing positive integer.

# Optimal Approach
Here we can't mark all the integers as we only have O(1) auxiliary space. So, we will use the same array to mark the numbers. But you'll think that how can we mark? There will be some number at each index. So, we will do this in loop until we reach the free space or come at begining, this way no data will be lost.

# Example
Array : [5, 6, 2, 1, 2] => N = 5
Pre Processing : We will remove all negatives integers and numbers greater than N by replacing them with 0.
0 = Represents position free to be marked, no loss of data.
-1 = Position already marked, integer present in input array.

Array (current state) : [6, 0, 2, 1, 2] 

Start with Index: 0
Read number 5 and free up position(index: 0) by marking it with 0. Mark number 5 by replacing arr[5 - 1] with -1. In order to avoid loss of data at index 4, we will keep it in temp variable. After marking, we will do the same process for temp variable which is 1.

Array (current state) : [-1, 0, 2, -1, 2] 
Insights - Integer 1 and 5 was present in input array because they are marked in above array.

Index : 1
Already 0. It's free space and we can ignore it.

Index : 2
2 will be marked at arr[2 - 1] which is already free so no further processing.
Array (current state) : [-1, -1, 0, -1, 2]

Index : 3
No data present to mark because it's -1.

Index : 4
2 will be marked at arr[2 - 1], it's already marked so we can either ignore or remark it.

Final array : [-1, -1, 0, -1, 0]

Traverse the array and stop at first non -1 number. Here it will be index 2, So Integer 3 is missing.

If we don't find any non -1 number then N + 1 will be the answer.


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N) - Since we will come at every index only once.

- Space complexity:
O(1) - No space is used other than few temporary variables.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int firstMissingPositive(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();

        // Remove negative and numbers greater than N, those are unwanted.
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (nums[i] < 0 || nums[i] > n) nums[i] = 0;
        }

        // Starting from index 0, we will start marking.
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (nums[i] == 0 || nums[i] == -1) continue;

            int index = nums[i] - 1; // index is the position of number which needs to be updated
            nums[i] = 0; 
            int temp;
            while (nums[index] > 0) {
                temp = nums[index];
                nums[index] = -1;
                index = temp - 1;
            }
            nums[index] = -1;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (nums[i] != -1) return i + 1;
        }
        return n + 1;
    }
};
```

