Suppose our head and position given to us as head = [4,5,6,7,8,9] & pos = 4

So, linked looks like-

  4 --> 5 --> 6 --> 7 --> 8 --> 9
                          ↑     ↓
						  ← ← ← ↓

						  So, their is a cycle at position 4,
						  therefore we have to return true as our answer
```
_____________
***Solution - I (Accepted)-***
* We maintain two pointers i.e slow and fast.
* Our fast pointer takes two step at a time and slow pointer is slow so he takes one step at a time.
* So, if their is a cycle present in our linked list, then no matter how fast our fast pointer moves. their is a time come when both i.e slow and fast pointer are standing on a same position.
* Why this happen? See, since our fast pointer taking two steps at a time,so by defaullt he will be always ahead of our slow pointer.
* But their is a cycle present in the linked list, our fast pointer end up in moving the cycle only.
* And their is a time came when both our fast and slow pointer stands up the same position.
* So, If fast and slow pointer cames to same position then we will return true by saying that yes their is a cycle in the linked list.
* But, Suppose if their is no cycle present in the linked list, then? 
* If their is no cyle present in the linked list then our fast pointer was the first one who reaches to the end.
* So if fast pointer reaches to the end, then we will say their is no cycle present in the linked list and hence return false.
* See below Image for better clarification.
_________________
* ![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/11e14acb-6005-4c2a-8ed5-59908440490a_1646713764.0097659.jpeg)
