We can solve this problem by using any of the 2 methods below-
***Please upvote if this explanation helps you.***

1. Using **Floyd's Cycle Finding Algorithm**-
Floyd’s cycle-finding algorithm is a pointer algorithm that uses only two pointers, moving through the sequence at different speeds. It states the usage of Linked List in this algorithm and its output.
The purpose is to determine whether the linked list has a cycle or not. First, we keep two pointers of the head node they are, **slow pointer** and **fast pointer**. At each iteration, you move one of the pointers by two steps and the other one by one step. So you have two pointers tortoise and the hare. Eventually one of the two cases will happen:

- **fastPointer** will reach the tail of the linked list(null), which means that there is no cycle in it
- **fastPointer** will meet **slowPointer**, which means that there is a cycle.


Let's understand by the below example-
Here the **Car M** is **SlowPointer** and **Car B** is **FastPointer**.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d5d5ace4-2acd-49e9-8426-ae1deefb2cd0_1648740035.1112502.png)
