The key idea is to use constraint `-10^5 <= Node.val <= 10^5`.
1. Choose value out of range, for example `Int32.MaxValue`
2. Traverse LinkedList
3. Mark all nodes with chosen value
4. Once we meet chosen value -> we have a cycle!
```
public class Solution {
    public bool HasCycle(ListNode head) {
        var cycle = Int32.MaxValue;
        while(head != null)
        {
            if(head.val == cycle) return true;
            head.val = cycle;
            head = head.next;
        }
        return false;
    }
}
```

